                  </hi>. I live in Steven-street, Bethnal-green-road. I went to bathe on the 18th of August, and left my trousers and money on the shore—when I came out all my things were gone—when I went into the water the prisoner was lying on a bar, which parted the field from the little path—a boy detected him, and took my clothes from him as I war running up the side of the canal naked—these are my clothes—I lost seven shillings, and 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 101/2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. was found on him—this handkerchief, which if mine, was returned with the clothes—they were taken by a boy not here.</p>
